			<Placemark>
				<name>Indasālaguhā</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A cave on the Vediya mountain, to the north of Ambasaṇḍā, which was a brahmin village, east of Rājagaha. Once, when the Buddha was staying there, Sakka visited him and asked him the questions recorded in the Sakkapañha Sutta. <span class="ref">DN.ii.263</span>]]></description>
