			<Placemark>
				<name>Kamboja / Kambojja / Kambuja / Kambujja / Kambojaka</name>
				<description><![CDATA[One of the sixteen Great Nations which, with Gandhāra, belonged, not to the Majjhimadesa but, evidently, to the Uttarāpatha. <span class="ref">AN.i.213</span><span class="ref">AN.iv.252</span><span class="ref">AN.iv.256</span><span class="ref">AN.iv.260</span></p><p>In the Assalāyana Sutta <span class="ref">MN.ii.149</span> it is stated that in Yona and in Kamboja, and also in the neighbouring countries, there were, in the Buddha’s time, only two classes of people, masters and slaves, and that a master could become a slave or vice versa. Elsewhere Kamboja is mentioned as a place not visited by women of other countries. <span class="ref">AN.ii.82</span>]]></description>
