				<name>Cātuma</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A Sākiyan village containing a mote-hall; near it was the Amalakīvana where the Buddha once stayed and preached the Cātuma Sutta. <span class="ref">MN.i.456<em>f.</em></span>]]></description>
