			<Placemark>
				<name>Cālikā</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A village near the Cālikapabbata visited by the Buddha. His attendant on one of these visits was Meghiya. Close to Cālikā was the village of Jantu where Meghiya went for alms. In the neighbourhood was the river Kimikālā, on whose banks was a mango grove. <span class="ref">AN.iv.354</span><span class="ref">Ud.iv.1</span>]]></description>
