				<name>Jīvakambavana</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A mango-grove in Rājagaha, belonging to Jīvaka, which he made over to the Buddha and his monks. He built a monastery in the grove, and there the Buddha stayed several times. On one such occasion Ajātasattu visited the Buddha and the Sāmaññaphala Sutta was preached. <span class="ref">DN.i.47<em>ff.</em></span>]]></description>
