				<name>Yona / Yavāna / Yonakā</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A country and its people. The name is probably the Pāḷi equivalent for Ionians, the Baktrian Greeks. The Yonas are mentioned with the Kambojas in the Assalāyana Sutta <span class="ref">MN.ii.149</span> as places in which there were only two classes of people, masters and slaves, and the master could become a slave or vice versa.]]></description>
