			<Placemark>
				<name>Vaṁsa</name>
				<description><![CDATA[The Vaṁsas and their country. It lay to the south of Kosala, and its capital was Kosambī on the Yamunā. Udena, son of Parantapa, was its king in the time of the Buddha.</p><p> Avanti lay to the south of the Vaṁsa country. The Vaṁsa were also called Vatsā. The country formed one of the sixteen Great Nations.</p><p>The district of Bhagga, in which was Suṁsumāragiri, seems to have been subject to the Vaṁsa in the Buddha’s time, for we find Udena’s son, Bodhi, living there. In nominal lists <span class="ref">DN.ii.200</span> the Vaṁsa are generally mentioned with the Ceti.]]></description>
