			<Placemark>
				<name>Hatthigāmaka</name>
				<description><![CDATA[A village on the road from Vesāli to Bhoganagara. It was the residence of Ugga-gahapati and is described as a village of the Vajjians.</p><p>The Buddha stayed there and was visited by Ugga. <span class="ref">AN.iv.212</span><span class="ref">SN.iv.109</span></p><p>On his last journey he again rested in the village. <span class="ref">DN.ii.123</span>]]></description>
